    <briefdescription>
<para>Additive White Gaussian Noise generator. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Generates complex CF32 samples where real and imaginary parts are independent zero-mean Gaussians, each with standard deviation <computeroutput>amplitude</computeroutput>. Total complex power = 2 * amplitude².</para>
<sect1 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md0_1s1"><sect2 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md0_1s2"><sect3 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md0">
<title>Algorithm</title><para>RNG: xoshiro256++ — four 64-bit state words, seeded via SplitMix64 from the user-supplied uint64 seed. Period 2^256 − 1.</para>
<para>Transform: Box-Muller. Each call to <ref refid="awgn__core_8h_1a507003634c145627b019aa27d98b9303" kindref="member">awgn_generate()</ref> consumes two 64-bit RNG outputs per complex output sample:</para>
<para>u1 ∈ (0, 1] (top 24 bits of first 64-bit word, +1 offset, /2^24) u2 ∈ [0, 1) (top 24 bits of second 64-bit word, /2^24) r = amplitude * sqrt(−2 · ln u1) θ = 2π · u2 out = r·cos θ + j·r·sin θ</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md1_1s1"><sect2 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md1_1s2"><sect3 id="awgn__core_8h_1autotoc_md1">
<title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structawgn__state__t" kindref="compound">awgn_state_t</ref><sp/>*g<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="awgn__core_8h_1a44e712fea4d4d3a1f7cc677ba9f85bbc" kindref="member">awgn_create</ref>(42,<sp/>1.0f);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>complex<sp/>out[1024];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="awgn__core_8h_1a507003634c145627b019aa27d98b9303" kindref="member">awgn_generate</ref>(g,<sp/>1024,<sp/>out);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="awgn__core_8h_1ac9b875533ec16bb6731207b366843f40" kindref="member">awgn_destroy</ref>(g);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
